om/news/music/sheffield-leadmill-bosses-claim-landlords-are-exterminating-them-after-they-denied-plans-to-close-venue-3195917">being “exterminated by the landlord”</a> before launching a fresh <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sheffields-leadmill-calls-on-fans-to-object-to-landlords-premises-licence-application-3444836">appeal to fans, asking for support after revealing that landlords were reportedly moving forward with eviction plans</a> .</p><p> Ahead of the rally next week, it has been revealed by <em><a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-south-yorkshire-66735507" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BBC News</a></em> that the venue have been offering £40 to &#39;volunteers&#39; in exchange for their support in opposing the venue&#39;s closure and to post on social media. </p><div class="ssrcss-11r1m41-RichTextComponentWrapper ep2nwvo0" data-component="text-block"><div class="ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"> When asked about the offer by <em>BBC News</em> , the venue said: “We are encouraging The Leadmill&#39;s supporters to attend a rally outside on that morning. </p></div></div><div class="ssrcss-11r1m41-RichTextComponentWrapper ep2nwvo0" data-component="text-block"><div class="ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"> “We don&#39;t know how many people will turn up and as The Leadmill staff will likely be in the hearing itself, we have teamed up with Gosh to ensure the rally is professionally and safely managed by some of their team outside. </p></div></div><div class="ssrcss-11r1m41-RichTextComponentWrapper ep2nwvo0" data-component="text-block"><div class="ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"> “Gosh are a company that we use regularly and we have a strong relationship with. They are obviously being paid for their time to do so.” </p><figure id="attachment_3323340" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3323340" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3323340" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/leadmill_Staff_2000.jpg" alt="The staff at Sheffield's Leadmill. Credit: The Leadmill" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/leadmill_Staff_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/leadmill_Staff_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/leadmill_Staff_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/leadmill_Staff_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/leadmill_Staff_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/leadmill_Staff_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3323340" class="wp-caption-text"> The staff at Sheffield&#39;s Leadmill. Credit: The Leadmill </figcaption></figure></div></div><div class="ssrcss-11r1m41-RichTextComponentWrapper ep2nwvo0" data-component="text-block"><div class="ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"> In response, Electric Group CEO Dominic Madden said: “[The] decision to resort to renting a crowd outside Sheffield Town Hall on the day of the licensing hearing is a clear indication that public interest in their campaign is waning. </p></div></div><div class="ssrcss-11r1m41-RichTextComponentWrapper ep2nwvo0" data-component="text-block"><div class="ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"> “Paying people £40 to stand outside of the hall is a move that reeks of cynicism, as it attempts to manipulate the licensing process and unduly influence Sheffield Council. </div></div><div class="ssrcss-11r1m41-RichTextComponentWrapper ep2nwvo0" data-component="text-block"><div class="ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"> “We&#39;ve consistently maintained that we will invest in the Leadmill to ensure it remains an inclusive, vibrant music and arts venue, of which Sheffield can be rightly proud for years to come.”</p></div></div><p> Ahead of the rally, a spokesperson for The Leadmill said: “If we don&#39;t stop this hostile takeover, the very soul and character of our great city is at risk.</p><p> “This landlord is exploiting a legal loophole to evict and destroy a highly regarded, independent, Sheffield success story, forcing us to cease trading, all for profit. But it&#39;s even worse than that.</p><p> “It couldn&#39;t be clearer. This is not just about The Leadmill. This is a fundamental Battle for the Soul of Sheffield. That&#39;s why we&#39;re asking you to help us win this battle. We need you to sign up and back our campaign.” </p><figure id="attachment_3286766" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3286766" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3286766" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3286766" class="wp-caption-text"> Richard Hawley and Jarvis Cocker onstage at the Leadmill in Sheffield on August 9. Credit: Tom Sunderland</figcaption></figure><p> Responding to the latest campaign, Madden told <i>NME: “</i> In 2016, Electric Group acquired the Leadmill building from MCR properties with a genuine concern for its future and the possibility of redevelopment. As operators of multiple music venues across the UK, it seemed only natural that we would step in to protect this iconic space.</p><p> “It&#39;s important to note that the current management&#39;s lease expired this year. Contrary to claims of exploiting a legal loophole, the reality is that a commercial lease has come to its natural end.”</p><p> He continued: “Phil Mills, the current operator of the Leadmill, had several opportunities to purchase the Freehold of the building, including during a public auction in 2014. However, he chose not to pursue this course of action, and as a result, Electric Group acquired the Freehold in 2016. Our intention from the beginning has been to continue operating the venue as a music, arts, and comedy hub, preserving its legacy.</p><p> “Our vision for the Leadmill is all about continuity of programming. We cherish the venue&#39;s history and the incredible talent it has nurtured over the years.”</p><p> Last year saw former <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jeremy-corbyn-joins-campaign-to-save-sheffield-leadmill-3227527">Labour leader Jeremy Corbyn visit The Leadmill and encourage others to “get behind it</a> “, echoing <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/leadmill-sheffield-eviction-closure-arctic-monkeys-tour-manager-local-reaction-3201505">the views of Sheffield locals</a> hailing it as “the heart of the city” and the likes of <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/local-stars-rally-around-leadmill-as-new-owners-register-for-name-electric-sheffield-3197594">Arctic Monkeys, Jarvis Cocker and Bring Me The Horizon&#39;s Oli Sykes among the Sheffield artists to have spoken out in support of the venue</a> .</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-leadmill-respond-after-offering-40-to-volunteers-to-attend-sheffield-rally-to-save-venue-3496055">The Leadmill respond after offering £40 to volunteers to attend Sheffield rally to save venue</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
新的人口普查发现，近一半的英国职业音乐家收入低于 1.4 万英镑https://www.nme.com/news/music/nearly-half-of-working-uk-musicians-earn-less-than-14k-new-census-finds-3496025?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=nearly-新人口普查发现，英国一半在职音乐家的收入低于 14,000 美元Will RichardsMon, 11 Sep 2023 10:08:48 +0000 Music NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3496025 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>根据新的人口普查，近一半的英国职业音乐家年收入低于 1.4 万英镑。阅读更多：英国脱欧：英国政府警告音乐家和工作人员“可能会发现自己集体失业” 新的音乐家普查调查了该国近 6,000 名活跃的音乐家，由音乐家联盟和帮助音乐家创建。其发现[...]</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nearly-half-of-working-uk-musicians-earn-less-than-14k-new-census-finds-3496025">新的人口普查发现，近一半英国职业音乐家的收入低于 1.4 万英镑，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/GLASTO_YUNGBLUD_JOHN-PEEL_-SATURDAY_EVA-PENTEL_2522-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>根据新的人口普查，近一半的英国职业音乐家年收入低于 1.4 万英镑。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li dir="auto"><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-touring-uk-house-of-lords-2022-artist-crew-unemployment-europe-3315337">英国脱欧：英国政府警告音乐家和工作人员“可能会发现自己集体失业”</a></strong></li></ul><p>新的音乐家普查调查了该国近 6,000 名活跃的音乐家，由音乐家联盟和帮助音乐家发起。</p><p>调查结果显示，尽管 70% 的参与者拥有学位或更高学历，但超过一半的受访者必须从事多种工作才能维持生计。</p><p>根据人口普查，一名音乐家平均拥有三到四份工作，全职从事音乐工作的人平均年薪仅为 3 万英镑，比英国平均工资中位数低近 5,000 英镑。</p><p>一位受访者表示，“在绩效工资方面存在真正的玻璃天花板，大多数绩效机会的费用与 20 年前相同。</p><p> “工作时间很不合群，排练常常是无薪的，而且周围还有很多无薪的等待。作为一名全职音乐家并试图以父母的身份出现实际上是不可能的，”他们补充道。 </p><figure id="attachment_3484378" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3484378" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3484378" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/primavera-barcelona-2023-peru.jpg" alt="2023 年巴塞罗那春之声" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/primavera-barcelona-2023-peru.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/primavera-barcelona-2023-peru-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/primavera-barcelona-2023-peru-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/primavera-barcelona-2023-peru-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/primavera-barcelona-2023-peru-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/primavera-barcelona-2023-peru-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3484378" class="wp-caption-text"> 2023 年 6 月 2 日，西班牙巴塞罗那，2023 年巴塞罗那 Primavera Sound 2023 第 3 天音乐会期间人群的景象（图片来源：Xavi Torrent/Redferns）</figcaption></figure><p>调查结果还指出，白人和非白人参与者之间的薪酬差距为 1,000 英镑，残疾人和非残疾人之间的薪酬差距是其四倍。</p><p>只有 32% 的非白人音乐家的全部收入来自音乐，而白人参与者的这一数字上升至 43%。</p><p>在讨论调查结果时，音乐家联盟秘书长内奥米·波尔 (Naomi Pohl) 表示，这些数据“为音乐家描绘了充满挑战的前景”，而“帮助音乐家”组织的老板莎拉·伍兹 (Sarah Woods) 补充道：“这也突显了音乐家们如何致力于继续创作我们都知道的音乐，并且爱;展示了我们的音乐家群体的真正韧性。”</p><p>今年夏天早些时候，有报道称，自英国<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/brexit">脱欧</a>以来<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/almost-50-per-cent-of-uk-musicians-working-less-in-europe-after-brexit-3487189">，近 50% 的英国音乐家在欧洲的工作量减少了</a>。</p><p> 《付出代价》报告的受访者中，47.4% 的人表示，英国脱欧后，他们在欧盟的工作量减少了，其中 27.8% 的人根本没有在欧洲大陆工作过。自 2021 年 1 月 1 日以来，40% 的人取消了工作，几乎同样多的人 (39%) 不得不拒绝计划中的工作。</p><p>早在 2021 年， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-industry-feel-theyve-been-dealt-a-no-deal-brexit-but-call-on-government-to-take-it-seriously-and-fix-it-2856716">英国音乐产业就曾共同公开表示，</a>当政府<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/government-rejects-visa-free-brexit-touring-petition-blames-eu-promises-help-navigate-changes-2875506">未能就音乐家和工作人员的免签证旅行和欧洲范围内的工作许可证进行谈判</a>时，他们实际上是如何遭遇“无协议脱欧”的。</p><p>结果，在新冠疫情之后，试图再次上路的艺术家们发现自己在英国脱欧后第一个夏天的欧洲巡演中走上了<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-one-year-on-music-industry-remain-frustrated-at-clueless-government-3130861">预期的“崎岖之路”</a> ——发现<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-touring-europe-strangling-talent-carnets-visa-merch-crew-government-response-summer-2022-3288735">英国脱欧的复杂性正在“扼杀下一代英国人才”在摇篮里”</a> 。</p><p>在上议院举行的听证会上，英国脱欧已经对那些希望前往欧洲巡演的人造成了损害，随后政府被警告称， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-touring-uk-house-of-lords-2022-artist-crew-unemployment-europe-3315337">音乐家和工作人员“可能会发现自己集体失业”</a> 。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nearly-half-of-working-uk-musicians-earn-less-than-14k-new-census-finds-3496025">新的人口普查发现，近一半英国职业音乐家的收入低于 1.4 万英镑，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
